physical_examinations.relevant_findings: 2 to 5 mm yellowish papules on the lateral aspect of her neck, expanding symmetrically to axillae, chest, abdomen, and inguinal region. Angioid streaks of the retina were detected.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: After 2 weeks of treatment with vitamin D3, new yellow papules (approximately 4-8 mm) developed on the neck and abdomen without itching or pain.

physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Biopsy findings of new papules showed thick epidermis and abundant calcium deposition compared with initial biopsy findings.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Electron microscopy revealed changes from electron-dense deposits to electron-lucent areas, suggesting unusual mineralization after treatment.
